    "The error detection module utilizes advanced natural language processing techniques to identify potential errors in the model's output in real-time, denoted by D.detect(x).",
    "The correction module, depicted as C.correct(x, e), employs a combination of rule-based and machine learning approaches to paint the full picture.",
    "if e ̸ = ∅ then 8:x ′ ← C.correct(x, e) ▷ Apply corrections based on detected errors9: L.log(x, e, x ′) ▷ Log original and corrected outputs with errors 10: else 11: x ′ ← x 12: end if 13:y ← x ′ ▷ Finalize the corrected output 14: end for B.",
    "Feedback Loop MechanismThe feedback loop mechanism is a pivotal component of the system, designed to perpetually enhance the model's learning and adaptation capabilities.",
    "This section elaborates on the mathematical rationale underlying the feedback loop's implementation, emphasizing its integration into the system's learning process through user interactions and automated adjustments.Let U i represent user feedback on instance i,F (U i) = 1 if error is verified 0 otherwise Define error impact function E(U i) = a • F (U i) + b,where a and b are constants determining the severity of the feedback."
